# EXAMPLE — SECRETS for the Copilot CLI capability.
# Target install path (NOT created by F6 step 2):
#   System-scope:  /etc/umbral/copilot-cli-secrets.env
#   User-scope:    ~/.config/openclaw/copilot-cli-secrets.env   ← canonical for Rick's VPS
# Required permissions when installed:
#   owner rick:rick, mode 0600
#
# Rick's live VPS uses the USER-SCOPE path under ~/.config/openclaw/.
# The /etc/umbral/* path is the system-scope fallback example only.
#
# RULES:
#   - NEVER commit a real value to this repo.
#   - Use ONLY COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN. No GH_TOKEN. No GITHUB_TOKEN.
#   - Token type: fine-grained PAT v2 with the "Copilot Requests" permission.
#       (OAuth Copilot CLI / OAuth gh-app tokens also acceptable when
#        running in equivalent non-interactive mode.)
#   - DO NOT use a classic PAT (ghp_*) — Copilot CLI does not support
#     it for non-interactive auth.
#   - DO NOT rely on `gh auth login` — that persists creds in
#     ~/.config/gh and is not used here.
#   - DO NOT persist the token to ~/.copilot/config.json.
#   - Rotate every <=90 days (PAT expiration). Revoke old PAT after restart.
#
# Placeholder (uncomment + replace ONLY in the live file at the install
# path, NEVER in this committed example):
# COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_<paste real fine-grained PAT v2 here>
